modules.description: This module provides predefined JSON-RPC error values for common server-side failure scenarios. It includes constants for parse errors, invalid requests, method not found, invalid parameters, and internal errors. These values are used directly in responses to client requests when specific error conditions occur during RPC handling.

This module implements a JSON-RPC server that processes incoming requests and routes them to registered callback functions. It works with JSON values and string-based RPC method names, producing JSON or string responses. Use this module to build a server that handles multiple RPC methods with custom logic, including error handling via predefined error codes.

This module implements the core data structures and serialization logic for JSON-RPC 2.0 messages. It defines types for requests, notifications, responses, and errors, along with functions to construct and serialize these messages to and from JSON and strings. It is used to build JSON-RPC clients and servers by providing direct manipulation of RPC message formats.
